HEADWORD: gegenschein
<hw>ge"gen*schein`</hw> <pr>(g⟦amac⟧"g⟦icr⟧n*sh⟦imac⟧n`)</pr>
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[German: counterglow.]</ety> <def>A faint patch of
light in the night sky that appears opposite the sun; a reflection of
sunlight by micrometeoric material in space.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> counterglow.</syn>⟦br⟧
